boston_s_innovation_district_creating_an.description:
On January 4, 2010, Mayor Menino announced the revisioning of the South Boston waterfront to be a place for tomorrow’s economy to thrive. The Innovation District is 1,000 acres of residential, commercial, and industrial space along the South Boston Waterfront, is intended to ensure Boston’s continued leadership in the innovation economy—both as an engine for job growth and the development of innovative products and services. 
